  "body": "After receiving a membership request for a community my account owns, I did get a sound but no visual indication. Without the sound I wouldn't know that I have received a request.\r\n\r\nThe chat view looks like this:\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-06-19 10-54-06](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/174473306-7c2fe8b6-408d-44ff-9622-3fdd6802e0db.png)\r\n\r\n^ I would at least expect a badge icon indicator in the community tab button on the left hand side.\r\nEven better, the \"membershipt request\" button we used to have\r\n\r\nHowever, I know i have a request because I sent it myself using a second desktop instance, so I go to the community view:\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-06-19 10-56-31](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/174473409-262f4f57-2559-4f55-878f-42d72a50611b.png)\r\n\r\n^ Also here, no visual indicator\r\n\r\nOnly after going to \"members\" I see a notification:\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-06-19 10-50-18](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/174473431-d9c37e7d-4cc5-4a0c-869d-c84b977418a7.png)\r\n\r\nUnfortunately it doesn't work but that's logged here: https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/6141",
